sion Sikshanamandira organises an education exhibition along with cultural programmes.				 																drama				 																																	 December 26 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Kushilav presents Rabindranath Tagores Chokher Bali. Drama: Partha Chattopadhyay; direction: Runu Chowdhury.				 																																	 December 26 at Rabindra Sadan: Aneeks 6th Ganga Yamuna Natya Utsav features (at 6.30 pm): Madhumala, directed by Ahmed Iqbal Haider and produced by Tirjak Natya Gosthi, Chattagram, Bangladesh. Also, as part of Aneeks inter-university short play competition, todays line-up: at Sisir Mancha; 6.30 pm: Chetona presents Nirnoy. Direction: Arun Mukhopadhyay; at Girish Mancha; 6.30 pm: Bengali Association, Nagpur presents Padmashree Pramila Datar. Direction: Chanchal Roy Chowdhury.				 																LECTURE				 																																	 December 26 at the Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Shivananda Hall; 5 pm: Dhyanesh Narayan Chakrabarti will speak on Mahabharater Shantiparba..				 																																	 December 26 at the Ramakrishna Vedanta Math; 7 pm: Dr Sasanka Bhushan Bandyopadhyay will speak on Brihadaranyaka Upanishad.				 																POETRY FESTIVAL				 																																	 December 27 at Srijan; 3.30 pm: Youth Poetry Festival, anchored by Nidhi Mehrotra and with comments by Dibyendu Palit, Nagendra Chourasia, Shahnaz Nabi and Sujata Sen. Anyone below 25 and write in English, Bengali, Hindi or Urdu may submit not more than five poems to the festival coordinator Saoni Banerjee (24249216 after 7.30 pm) or e-mail at srijan2000vsnl.net				 																WORKSHOP				 																																	 December 26 at Thoughtshop Foundation, 188/90 Prince Anwar Shah Road; 4 pm - 6 pm: Thoughtshop Foundation conducts a workshop on assertiveness (age group: 17-25 years). Call /9 to register.				 																																	 December 27 at Skill Sharpeners, 110 Asutosh Mukherjee Road,